addAggregator(address).details: Adds a Dex aggregator address to the whitelist

params.token: The address of the ERC20 token

beneficiaryWithdrawStable(uint256,addres.details: Withdraws the beneficiary's available balance to release (fulfilled with success). Only the fulfiller can withdraw the releaseable pool.

fulfillAndSwap(uint256,(uint256,string,s.details: Registers a fulfillment result and swaps from native currency both releaseable pool and accumulated fees to stablecoins in a single transaction. The swap is done using an off-chain generated Dex aggregator call.

params.swapData: The struct capturing the aggregator call data, tokens, and amounts.

fulfillERC20AndSwap(uint256,(uint256,str.details: Registers a fulfillment result and swaps both releaseable pool and accumulated fees to stablecoins in a single transaction. The swap is done using an off-chain generated Dex aggregator call.

params.swapData: The struct capturing the aggregator call data, tokens, and amounts.

isAggregator(address).details: Checks if an address is a Dex aggregator

myFees(address).details: Returns the fulfiller's fees for a given token

myFeesNative(address).details: Returns the fulfiller's fees for a given token on the native contract

myPool(address).details: Returns the fulfiller's pool for a given token

myPoolNative(address).details: Returns the fulfiller's pool for a given token on the native contract

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.erc20Escrow_: The address of the ERC20 escrow.

params.feeAmountBasisPoints: The fee amount percentage for the service

params.serviceRegistry_: The address of the service registry.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

withdrawAccumulatedFeesStable(uint256,ad.details: Withdraws the accumulated fees for a given service ID. Only the fulfiller can withdraw the accumulated fees.

params.token: The address of the ERC20 token

withdrawERC20FulfillerPoolAndFees(addres.details: Withdraws the fulfiller's ERC20 pool and feesOnly the fulfiller can withdraw the releaseable pool and fees

withdrawFulfillerStablePoolAndFees(addre.details: Withdraws the fulfiller's stablecoin pool and fees from the native contractOnly the fulfiller can withdraw the releaseable pool and fees

beneficiaryWithdraw(uint256).notice: This method must only be called by the service fulfiller.

beneficiaryWithdrawERC20(uint256,address.notice: This method must only be called by the service fulfiller.

registerERC20Fulfillment(uint256,(uint25.notice: This method must only be called by the service fulfiller or the owner It registers a fulfillment result for a service calling the escrow contract.

registerFulfillment(uint256,(uint256,str.notice: This method must only be called by the service fulfiller or the owner It registers a fulfillment result for a service calling the escrow contract.

setService(uint256,uint16,address,addres.notice: This method must only be called by an owner. It sets up a service escrow address and validator address.  The escrow is intended to be a valid Bando escrow contract  The validator address is intended to be a contract that validates the service's identifier. eg. phone number, bill number, etc.

setServiceFulfillmentFee(uint256,uint16).notice: This method must only be called by the owner. It sets up the fulfillment fee percentage for a service.

setServiceRef(uint256,string).notice: This method must only be called by the owner. It sets up a service reference for a service.

withdrawERC20Fees(uint256,address).notice: This method must only be called by the owner.

withdrawNativeFees(uint256).notice: This method must only be called by the owner.
